+              >
+                <div class="pf-v6-c-content">
+                  <h1>Code of Conduct</h1>
+
+                  <h3>1. Our Pledge</h3>
+                  <p>
+                    In the interest of fostering an open and welcoming
+                    environment, we as members, contributors, and leaders of our
+                    organization, commit to making participation in our
+                    community a harassment-free experience for everyone,
+                    regardless of age, body size, visible or invisible
+                    disability, ethnicity, gender identity and expression, level
+                    of experience, nationality, personal appearance, race,
+                    religion, or sexual identity and orientation.
+                  </p>
+
+                  <h3>2. Our Standards</h3>
+                  <ul>
+                    <li>
+                      <b>Respectful Communication:</b> We prioritize respectful
+                      and professional communication, even during disagreements.
+                      We value constructive criticism and feedback, and we do
+                      not tolerate personal attacks, insults, or derogatory
+                      comments.
+                    </li>
+                    <li>
+                      <b>Inclusivity:</b> We are committed to ensuring a
+                      welcoming environment for everyone. Discrimination or
+                      exclusionary behavior is not tolerated.
+                    </li>
+                    <li>
+                      <b>Collaboration:</b> We encourage collaboration and
+                      cooperation. We seek to build on the collective strength
+                      of our diverse community, and we value the sharing of
+                      ideas, knowledge, and experience.
+                    </li>
+                    <li>
+                      <b>Responsibility:</b> We expect all members to take
+                      responsibility for their actions. Apologies should be
+                      given where appropriate, with a commitment to learn from
+                      mistakes.
+                    </li>
+                  </ul>
+
+                  <h3>3. Our Responsibilities</h3>
+                  <p>
+                    Community leaders are responsible for clarifying the
+                    standards of acceptable behavior and are expected to take
+                    appropriate and fair corrective action in response to any
+                    instances of unacceptable behavior.
+                  </p>
+                  <p>
+                    Community leaders have the right and responsibility to
+                    remove, edit, or reject comments, code, wiki edits, commits,
+                    issues, and other contributions that are not aligned with
+                    this Code of Conduct.
+                  </p>
+
+                  <h3>4. Reporting &amp; Enforcement</h3>
+                  <p>
+                    Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable
+                    behavior may be reported by contacting the community team
+                    via our <a href="#connect">Connect page</a>. The team will
+                    review and investigate all complaints, and will respond in a
+                    way that it deems appropriate to the circumstances.
+                  </p>
+
+                  <h3>5. Changes to this Code of Conduct</h3>
+                  <p>
+                    The VanLUG organization reserves the right to revise,
+                    update, or change this Code of Conduct at any time. The
+                    community will be notified of any significant changes.
+                  </p>
+
+                  <h3>6. Conclusion</h3>
+                  <p>
+                    We aim to foster a community that is welcoming, inclusive,
+                    and supportive. We encourage all members to help us create a
+                    safe and positive environment. By participating in this
+                    community, you agree to adhere to this Code of Conduct.
+                  </p>
+                  <p>
+                    This is a living document and we encourage all members to
+                    suggest changes or improvements as our community grows and
+                    evolves.
+                  </p>
